  <archdesc level="collection">
    <did>
      <unitid>NCBS-2026-001</unitid>
      <unittitle>Pioneers of Biological Sciences in India Collection</unittitle>
      <unitdate normal="1950/2020">1950-2020</unitdate>
      <physdesc>
        <extent>3 linear feet</extent>
        <extent>approximately 1,200 items</extent>
      </physdesc>
      <langmaterial>
        <language langcode="eng">English</language>
        <language langcode="hin">Hindi</language>
      </langmaterial>
      <abstract>
        This collection documents the contributions of pioneering scientists 
        to biological sciences research in India from 1950 to 2020. Materials 
        include correspondence, research notes, photographs, conference papers, 
        and institutional records that collectively preserve the history of 
        science in contemporary India.
      </abstract>
      <repository>
        <corpname>Archives at NCBS-TIFR</corpname>
      </repository>
    </did>

    <bioghist>
      <head>Historical Note</head>
      <p>
        The National Centre for Biological Sciences (NCBS), established in 1991 
        as a centre of the Tata Institute of Fundamental Research (TIFR), has 
        been at the forefront of biological sciences research in India. The 
        Archives at NCBS serves as a public collecting centre for the history 
        of science in contemporary India, preserving records of scientists, 
        institutions, and research traditions that have shaped Indian biology.
      </p>
    </bioghist>

    <scopecontent>
      <head>Scope and Content</head>
      <p>
        This collection comprises personal papers, institutional records, 
        and research documentation from leading figures in Indian biological 
        sciences. Materials span seven decades of scientific inquiry and 
        include both physical and born-digital records.
      </p>
    </scopecontent>

    <accessrestrict>
      <head>Access Restrictions</head>
      <p>
        This collection is open for research. Some materials may require 
        advance appointment. Digital reproductions available upon request.
      </p>
    </accessrestrict>

    <userestrict>
      <head>Use Restrictions</head>
      <p>
        Copyright held by NCBS-TIFR. Permission required for publication. 
        Single copies may be made for personal research use.
      </p>
    </userestrict>

